Iavan Pijoos, News24(iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg - A man believed to be in his fifties was shot while waiting for a pupil outside the Rivonia Primary School gates in Sandton on Tuesday, Emer-G-Med said.&nbsp; Spokesperson Max Cohen said the man had been shot after an alleged armed robbery and suspected attempted hijacking. "He sustained a gunshot wound to one of his legs during a scuffle between him and the armed assailants," Cohen said adding that the man was in serious condition. The suspect fled with the man's watch.The incident happened at about 13:50 on Tuesday afternoon.&nbsp;Police and the school could not be reached for comment. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.